  "text": "Ring Battery Doorbell Plus $90 $150 Save $60 The Ring Battery Video Doorbell Plus offers sharp 1536p HD+ video with color night vision for clear, full-body views in any light. It connects on 2.4GHz Wi-Fi and lasts up to eight months per charge—no need for constant recharging. Picking out a video doorbell isn’t just about grabbing the first one you see; it’s all about figuring out what features matter most to you. Do you need crisp video quality? Smart alerts? Easy installation? Also, where you’re planning to mount it can make a big difference in which model works best. Whether you’re looking for an affordable way to boost home security or taking the first step toward a fully connected smart home, a Ring video doorbell could be a solid choice. Currently, you can snag the Ring Battery Doorbell Plus for just $90 on Woot, down from its usual $150. That’s a solid $60 in savings. But don’t wait too long—this deal is only around for a month or until it sells out. What's great about the Ring Battery Doorbell Plus? This smart doorbell lets you see everything thanks to its full HD, head-to-toe view and wide-angle coverage, all accessible through the Ring app. No more awkward, half-cut views; you’ll see faces, packages, and everything in between. With customizable motion zones, you can cut down on unnecessary alerts and get notified only when it really matters. Plus, this doorbell doesn’t miss a trick even after dark. It boasts color night vision, motion-triggered alerts, package notifications, and two-way talk with Alexa support—so you can chat with visitors right from your phone. Not home? No problem. Use two-way audio to respond in real time or set up quick replies to handle things hands-free. Related Ring Battery Doorbell Plus review: A porch pirate's nightmare A good doorbell that’s most useful if you get lots of deliveries With color night vision, you’ll get clear, detailed footage even in low light, eliminating blurry, black-and-white recordings at night. And the swappable battery design means you can switch out the battery in seconds without taking the whole doorbell down just to recharge. And the battery is a standout feature in our review. Unlike complicated security setups, installing the Ring Battery Doorbell Plus is a breeze. Just pop in the rechargeable battery, connect it to the app, mount it with the included screws, and snap on the faceplate. Related",
