affordable way to boost home security or taking the first step toward a fully connected smart home, a Ring video doorbell could be a solid choice.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eCurrently, you can snag the \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/ring-battery-doorbell-plus-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRing Battery Doorbell Plus\u003c/a\u003e for just $90 on Woot, down from its usual $150. That’s a solid $60 in savings. But don’t wait too long—this deal is only around for a month or until it sells out.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-ring-battery-doorbell-plus\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Ring Battery Doorbell Plus?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eThis smart doorbell lets you see everything thanks to its full HD, head-to-toe view and wide-angle coverage, all accessible through the Ring app. No more awkward, half-cut views; you’ll see faces, packages, and everything in between. With customizable motion zones, you can cut down on unnecessary alerts and get notified only when it really matters.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003ePlus, this doorbell doesn’t miss a trick even after dark. It boasts color night vision, motion-triggered alerts, package notifications, and two-way talk with Alexa support—so you can chat with visitors right from your phone. Not home? No problem. Use two-way audio to respond in real time or set up quick replies to handle